imple way to value the business is to say that the fair value of the busine=
ss is generally ~100 cents on the dollar in liquidating value and another ~=
130 cents on the dollar in franchise value. If that liquidating value has b=
een vaporized by a rates bet, the surviving business is still worth a premi=
um to book.</p></blockquote>
